programme.title: Kirstie's Handmade Christmas
programme.desc: The presenter heads to London to experience Columbia Road's Christmas night market in Hoxton, featuring mulled wine, carols and `urban chic' sensibilities. The event also plays host to an array of shops selling hand-made gifts and goodies. Plus, some of Britain's most accomplished crafts-people compete in three more festive contests, this time taking in floral arrangements, fabulous decorations, and `alternative' Christmas dishes. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Christmas Magic
programme.desc: A woman dies in a car accident, but is sent back to the land of the living by her spirit guide to perform one last good deed. She must help a single father whose business is failing to turn his life around by Christmas, but her feelings for him complicate the assignment. Fantasy, starring Lindy Booth and Paul McGillion.(n)

programme.title: A Christmas Proposal
programme.desc: A lawyer visits a mountain town his client wants to demolish and turn into a ski resort, where he learns the attorney fighting the plan is his old childhood sweetheart. When a car accident leaves him stranded, he finds his feelings for his opponent come flooding back. Romantic comedy, starring Nicole Eggert and David O'Donnell.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp and Phil Spencer head to Devon, where they help local newlyweds Sam and Jamie, who are looking to start afresh in a new home and put a difficult two years behind them. Plus, Sharon wants to move to Torquay with husband Geoff, as well as her children and mother, but the couple have never viewed a house together and it soon becomes apparent the property experts will have a tough time persuading them to agree on a new home.(n)

programme.title: Jamie's Night Before Christmas
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver returns to help the viewers raise their seasonal game with foolproof recipes and clever last-minute ways to improve their festive dishes. Having surveyed thousands of Brits to find out what ingredients they have bought, what is on their menus and what they already have in their cupboards, Jamie looks at what people fear most about cooking on Christmas Day - from getting the timings right to soggy roast potatoes or a dry turkey - and presents tips to make Christmas dinner classics taste better than ever.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away
programme.sub-title: Canary Islands v Isle of Wight.
programme.desc: Neil Smith and his partner Steph Grzyb regularly take holidays in Fuerteventura in the Canary Islands, where Neil can play golf in guaranteed sunshine. He would love to live there full-time, but Steph would rather settle on the Isle of Wight. Jasmine Harman and Sara Damergi are on hand to offer advice on the pros and cons of either move.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away
programme.desc: Jasmine Harman and Sara Damergi help retired couple Matthew and Myra McGuigan search for a new home in either Cheltenham, Gloucestershire, or Spain's Costa del Sol. The couple have already sold their UK house and are looking to find another property quickly.(n)

programme.title: The Secret Life of the Zoo
programme.sub-title: The Secret Life of the Zoo at Christmas.
programme.desc: With Christmas fast approaching, the keepers try to get the animals into the festive spirit. Stockings have been hung for the Sumatran orang-utan family, only for eight-year-old Indah to open everyone's for then. There is concern about the health of reticulated python Bali, who has been off her food for more than three months. She needs a check-up, but at 23ft it takes 10 brave keepers to catch her. Malayan tapirs Marjorie and Bitong welcome a baby, although However, the new dad is not happy when his daughter comes between him and his partner, and sun bear couple Tony and Millie's relationship is growing stale - will a trial separation help?.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Wildest Weather
programme.desc: Footage of unusual weather conditions recorded in Britain during 2016, and exploring the factors that led to these incidents. The programme features footage recorded by people caught in the middle of floods, super-storms, tornadoes and lightning strikes, as well as a look at how a record level El Nino effect altered Britain's weather.(n)

programme.title: The Supervet
programme.desc: Festive edition of the documentary following the work of Professor Noel Fitzpatrick and his team. Charity worker Kerry brings in Maxi, a three-year old rescue greyhound with severely damaged front legs. Noel's dog Keira is rushed into the practice with sickness and diarrhoea. The team also treats River, a Border terrier puppy who has fractured both back legs, and Noel makes a surprise visit home to Ireland.(n)

programme.title: Gogglebox
programme.desc: The nation's favourite armchair critics share their opinions on what they have been watching during the week, including Strictly Come Dancing, Planet Earth II, First Dates, Rillington Place, David Blaine: Beyond Magic, The Big Life Fix with Simon Reeve, When Phillip Met Prince Philip and White Christmas.(n)

programme.title: The World's Most Expensive Toys
programme.desc: While the general public search out bargain toys on the high street and online, the UK's millionaires and billionaires use a network of bespoke, high-end suppliers of luxurious gifts and entertainment. This documentary explores the world of the craftspeople and inventors attempting to realise the dreams of Britain's wealthiest by creating luxurious gifts and entertainments, with this network of bespoke, high-end suppliers making everything from crystal-encrusted rocking horses to £22,500 doll's houses.(n)

programme.title: It Was Alright In
programme.desc: Matt Lucas narrates this look at the programmes that flirted with danger during the decade, including Blue Peter, which carried on filming as a fire broke out live on air, while The Fun of the Fair showed teenage girls riding motorcycles through burning hoops. At the same time government-produced public information films petrified viewers with scary scenarios of possible accidents in the home. Contributors include Robin Askwith, Liza Goddard, Oona King, Clive Anderson, Philippa Perry, Samira Ahmed, Ellie Taylor and Angela Barnes.(n)

programme.title: Parents Do the Funniest Things
programme.desc: A look at modern family life from the children's point of view, offering their thoughts on what their parents do, and their views on how the adult world works in general.(n)

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: The staff at St George's A&E in south-west London tend to 59-year-old Debbie, who cut her hand on her lawnmower while distracted by thoughts of her son's forthcoming wedding. Also visiting the emergency room is 70-year-old George, whose eye has been impaled by a piece of driftwood, after he fell while bailing rainwater from his boat moored on the Thames. Plus, eight-year-old Phoebe arrives after accidentally sitting on a pair of scissors she left on a chair - getting them stuck in her thigh.(n)

programme.title: Alan Carr's 12 Stars of Christmas
programme.desc: Michelle Keegan, Josh Widdicombe and Louis Walsh are the contestants helping the audience tonight on the celebrity quiz, answering questions posed by the stars hidden behind Alan's giant advent calendar - Miranda Hart, Will.i.am, Matt Lucas, Jessica Ennis-Hill, Roger Moore, Little Mix, Bear Grylls and William Shatner. Kate Humble also joins in the fun.(n)

programme.title: Coast vs Country
programme.desc: David and Anne are now semi-retired and spend half the year in Costa Rica, but the rest of the time they want to live in David's childhood home of east Scotland. Anne loves the beach and is relying on coastal property finder Kerr Drummond to make her dream come true. However, David is certain the space they want for the budget they have can only be found in the countryside, and it's up to Sara Damergi to prove her country credentials and deliver. She and Kerr compete to find the perfect property for a budget of £150,000.(n)

programme.desc: A festive celebrity special of the culinary competition featuring TV presenter Rav Wilding, Olympic swimmer Rebecca Adlington, TV personality Jennifer Ellison, actor Alex Carter and Mrs Moneypenny from consumer programme SuperScrimpers.(n)

programme.title: Nothing Like the Holidays
programme.desc: An injured soldier returns home to spend Christmas with his family after serving overseas, also hoping to track down his lost love. He finds his siblings have problems of their own to cope with, while his mother is planning to divorce his secretive father. Comedy drama, starring Alfred Molina, Freddy Rodriguez, Elizabeth Pena and John Leguizamo.(n)

programme.title: The Holiday Tree
programme.desc: A publishing assistant is disappointed to learn that her parents' Christmas tree farm is being threatened with closure. She orders a tree from them for her boss, and discovers it is a sapling she remembers from a childhood experience. The event inspires her to take the tree home and try to save the family business. Festive drama, starring Lacey Chabert and Corey Sevier.(n)

programme.title: All About Christmas Eve
programme.desc: A New York high-society party planner's life hinges on whether or not she gets a plane to Los Angeles on Christmas Eve. In one version of her life, she makes the flight and takes on a job that could make her career, but in an alternative scenario, she sacrifices the opportunity for a festive holiday with her boyfriend. Romantic drama, with Haylie Duff and Chris Carmack.(n)

programme.title: Deal or No Deal on Tour
programme.sub-title: Deal or No Deal on Tour.
programme.desc: The Tour reaches its last stop as the Banker takes Noel Edmonds and the team to Glasgow to play the game at the Kelvingrove Art Gallery and Museum. With bagpipes, drummers, an organist and the biggest live audience the show has ever had, this Christmas spectacular is a fitting end to the national tour. As usual, contestants try to guess the values of mystery boxes containing as much as £250,000.(n)

programme.title: Tree of the Year with Ardal O'Hanlon
programme.desc: The comedian and former Father Ted actor visits some of the UK's most remarkable trees, before revealing the winners of the Woodland Trust's prestigious Tree of the Year awards from a 28-strong shortlist. Each winning specimen from England, Scotland, Northern Ireland and Wales is then put to a panel of experts, who select just one of the four to take the overall title of UK Tree of the Year.(n)

programme.title: Jamie's Ultimate Christmas
programme.desc: Jamie Oliver has been cooking and experimenting with classic Christmas food for over two decades and this programme pulls together his knowledge and experience to bring the very best of the season. He begins with what he calls the three foundations of Christmas, with guests will forgiving any mistakes as long as the turkey is succulent, the gravy is tasty, and the roast potatoes are perfect, and serves the main course with Brussels sprouts done with chorizo and chestnuts, and glazed carrots. Jamie also shares some other dishes, including gravadlax steeped in a beetroot, horseradish and vodka marinade, as well as gooey chocolate pots, turkey risotto, cocktails, and a classic beef Wellington.(n)

programme.title: First Dates
programme.desc: Festive edition of the restaurant-based dating show in which Fred and his team open up the restaurant to help 10 new singletons find love in time for Christmas. Operations manager Yasmin, 29, is matched with 31-year-old dental practice manager Ryan, while 59-year-old Mandi is looking for someone with whom to enjoy. Will 65-year-old antique expert Robert be to her taste? Make-up artist Sophie, 24, sits down with 34-year-old window cleaner and self-proclaimed traditional gentleman Mehmet, while embroidery designer Scott is partnered with gallery assistant Jim. The pair discuss culture and the arts, but will they see the beauty in each other?.(n)

programme.title: Celebrity First Dates
programme.desc: TV presenter Esther Rantzen has found life lonely since the death of her husband Desmond Wilcox in 2000, but is worried her formidable reputation can scare men off. She participates in this celebrity version of the show in which singletons meet up with potential partners at a restaurant. Also appearing on this first edition are actor Richard Blackwood (aka EastEnders bad boy Vincent), The Only Way Is Essex reality TV star Jess Wright and 2012 Paralympics table tennis silver medallist Will Bayley.(n)

programme.sub-title: The Yorkshire Vet: Winter on the Moors.
programme.desc: Called out to remote farms to tend animals in labour and the sick and injured, vets Julian Norton and Peter Wright must contend with dark, cold nights, rain and snow as they battle to treat and save patients, including owls and cattle.(n)

programme.title: Make You Laugh Out Loud
programme.sub-title: Santa Makes You Laugh Out Loud.
programme.desc: Comedians Zoe Lyons, Ellie Taylor and Marlon Davis present a seasonal clip show featuring some of the funniest Christmas-themed videos currently doing the rounds online. Among the disastrous 'Santa fails', Christmas dinner disasters and grumpy dressed-up pets, the trio also highlight the stories behind popular yuletide videos, including the story of the bearded shopper who decided to play along when a three-year-old passer-by mistook him for Father Christmas, and Norman the bull mastiff, who hates Christmas and all associated songs. Narrated by Iain Lee.(n)

programme.desc: The debt collection agents grapple with emotional evictions and moral dilemmas during the festive period, including a young family in Crystal Palace who are made homeless when the landlord repossesses their home because he wants to redevelop the property. The eviction comes as a shock to the family as they are up-to-date with their rent, but have just one hour to gather their belongings. Plus, an acrimonious divorce in Chessington comes to a head when the estranged wife obtains a writ to reclaim the house, and an off-licence owner in Hampshire with unpaid rent of more than £5,000 battles to keep his business open just as everything shuts down for the holidays.(n)

programme.desc: A zesty soundtrack spices up this stirring but tragic profile of pioneering Latino salsa singer Hector Lavoe (Marc Anthony), who was popular in the 1960s, '70s and '80s. Jennifer Lopez, Anthony's real-life wife, costars as his spouse, and the cinematic sparks fly when the two are onscreen. Lopez also served as producer. Directed by Leon Ichaso, who co-wrote the script with David Darmstaedter and Todd Anthony Bello. John Ortiz, Manny Perez, Federico Castelluccio, Vincent Laresca, Romi Diaz(n)

programme.title: The Longest Ride

programme.title: Who Wants to Be a Millionaire
programme.desc: Although the once-hot game show Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? had lost its luster as a prime-time ABC offering, the producers felt that there was enough life left in the property to warrant a Monday-through-Friday syndicated version. Taking over from the earlier series' host Regis Philbin was Meredith Vieira of The View. To make certain that the series would not be bankrupted after its first week on the air, the questions posed to contestants were considerably harder than those on the prime-time incarnation. Also, the famous "fastest finger" round was eliminated, taking some of the pressure off the contestants when they struggled to come up with answers. The most noteworthy change from the original version was the absence of Regis Philbin's familiar catchphrases: One would never hear Meredith Vieira chime in with the legendary "Is that your final answer?" The syndicated Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? was launched on September 16, 2002(n)

programme.title: The Three Stooges
programme.desc: Listen Judge. It's time to get Shemped with this home video collection, which serves up three Three Stooges shorts featuring Shemp Howard, Larry Fine, and Moe Howard at their comic best. Listen Judge finds the Stooges charged with vagrancy, so they try to be on their best behavior when they're hired to repair a wealthy woman's doorbell -- but after they scare away the servants, the boys wind up helping the lady of the house stage a birthday party that soon becomes a disaster. Moe, Larry, and Shemp invent a youth elixir in Bubble Trouble; their landlord (who is ready to evict them) is impressed when the potion shaves a couple decades off of his wife, but when he takes a bit too much himself, the results are surprising! And in Dunked in the Deep, the Stooges discover that their next door neighbor is a spy working for an enemy nation. He's stashed some secret microfilm inside a melon, and the boys are determined to find it and turn their neighbor over to the police, before the information falls into the wrong hands(n)

programme.title: Prancer
programme.desc: Seasonal tale about a young girl who, separated from her father, is desperate to keep the spirit of Christmas alive in a small American town where joy and goodwill have long been absent. She finds inspiration in the miraculous appearance of an injured reindeer, which she believes to be one of Santa's team, nursing it back to health before trying to return the majestic animal - nicknamed Prancer - to Santa Claus(n)

programme.title: Santa Claus: The Movie
programme.desc: An eager-to-please elf teams up with Santa Claus to save the spirit of Christmas from the evil influence of a villainous toy tycoon who wants to flood the world with very dangerous playthings(n)

programme.title: A Christmas Carol

programme.title: Four Christmases
programme.desc: Reese Witherspoon and Vince Vaughn star in Seth Gordon's frothy romcom about a happily unmarried couple who reconsider their relationship after spending Christmas with their families. Brad and Kate usually avoid family Christmases by booking blow-out holidays. But when dense fog grounds their flight to Fiji, they have no choice but to see each of their divorced parents - whom they've never introduced one another to - on the same day. Brad's dad Howard mixes insults about Brad's masculinity with criticisms of his Christmas presents, his cage-fighting brothers embarrass him, while hippy mum shows off her latest toy boy. The pair fare no better when they meet Kate's born-again Christian mum, her brash older sister Courtney and her father. As the day progresses, Kate and Brad find out more about each other and start having doubts about their relationship - to the point where they start to fear they can no longer reconcile their differences..(n)

programme.title: Deck the Halls

programme.title: Off-Air
programme.desc: Off-Air(n)

programme.desc: An Interpol agent undertakes a mission to recover a deadly weapon of mass destruction(n)

programme.title: MacArthur
programme.desc: The life of General Douglas MacArthur is covered from Corregidor in 1942 to his dismissal by President Truman during the Korean War(n)

programme.title: Under Siege
programme.desc: Casey Ryback is a former Navy SEAL captain who is now the cook aboard the USS Missouri. Everyone aboard is about to celebrate the birthday of Captain Adams. They've even hired a band led by William Strannix, and former playboy playmate Jordan Tate to jump out of a cake and dance. What Adams doesn't know is that he is in for a deadly surprise(n)

programme.title: Remember the Titans
programme.desc: The appointment of black coach Herman Boone to a high school in 70s Virginia causes a stir in the town, where white coach Yoast is well-respected. Boone walks into a minefield of bigotry but his fair-minded approach gradually wins the hearts of his players. A tub-thumping, passionate tale based on a true story(n)

programme.title: Ali
programme.desc: The one-two knockout punch of Will Smith as Muhammad Ali and Jon Voight as Howard Cosell (both received Oscar nominations) drives this triumphant sports bio. Smith perfectly embodies the former heavyweight champ and director Michael Mann does an outstanding job capturing the action in the ring. Jamie Foxx, Mario Van Peebles, Ron Silver(n)

programme.title: Kiss the Girls
programme.desc: Washington, D.C., forensic psychologist Dr. Alex Cross is also a best-selling author. After his niece Naomi is reported missing, he heads his Porsche for Durham, North Carolina, where eight young women have been reported missing. Bodies are found by local policemen, along with the killer's signature, Casanova(n)

programme.title: The Conjuring
programme.desc: Paranormal investigators battle a malevolent entity that's haunting a family living in a remote farmhouse in this terrifying tale of the supernatural(n)

programme.title: The Wrestler
programme.desc: In the late 80's, the wrestler Randy Robinson is at the peak of his career. Twenty years later, his stardom is nothing but a memory, but his passion for the sport keeps him going(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike
programme.desc: Channing Tatum and Alex Pettyfer star in Steven Soderbergh's drama about male strippers in Florida. Drawing partly on his own real-life experiences of stripping when he was a teen, Tatum plays the movie's eponymous central character. Mike is in his 30s and has for some time earned his living by disrobing for the cash-paying audiences who frequent the Xquisite All-Male Revue. However, he's given reason to reassess the way his life is going when a new young recruit, Adam, joins the team. The enthusiasm with which Adam embraces his new lifestyle only serves to sharpen Mike's awareness of its shallowness; and then there's Adam's sister Brooke, who Mike begins to fall in love with..(n)

programme.title: The Last Witch Hunter
programme.desc: An immortal witch hunter joins forces with a witch to stop a plague that could decimate the population of New York City(n)

programme.title: Dance of the Dead
programme.desc: As prom gets underway and the dead come out to play, the only hope for saving the day is the mismatched couple that can't seem to agree on anything. As the Cosa High School Senior Prom draws near, the local teens are more preoccupied with getting laid and looking good on the big night. But while local teen Jimmy (Jared Kusnitz) seems completely unfazed by all the infectious enthusiasm that's spreading through the student body, his girlfriend Lindsey (Greyson Chadwick) has thrown herself into the teenage ritual and remains determined to have the perfect romantic evening. But it's kind of difficult to enjoy an intimate dance when your classmates are trying to eat your brains, and when the tux-clad teens begin turning blue and munching on flesh, Jimmy and Lindsey are forced to put their differences aside long enough to extinguish the zombie plague before it spreads beyond campus grounds(n)

programme.title: Ready to Rumble
programme.desc: Can two inept amateurs help a fading wrestling star make a comeback? A veteran professional wrestler (Oliver Platt) is no longer winning matches, thus disappointing his fans, especially a pair of grappling enthusiasts (David Arquette and Scott Caan) who regard the aging fighter as their hero. They come up with what they believe is a foolproof plan to put their favorite fighter back on top: they'll pose as a wrestling tag team, stage a match with their favorite, lose in a truly embarrassing manner, and thus clear the way for his comeback. But is returning to the top of the card really this simple? Ready to Rumble also features Martin Landau and Rose McGowan, with several stars from the WCW professional wrestling league playing themselves, including Bill Goldberg(n)

programme.title: Battle for the Planet of the Apes
programme.desc: The fifth and last chapter of the series finds the simians fighting a band of radiation-scarred mutants(n)

programme.title: Doomsday
programme.desc: "28 Days Later" meets "The Road Warrior" and "Escape From New York" in this action-packed thriller about efforts to contain a deadly virus spreading across post-apocalyptic Great Britain. Rhona Mitra, Bob Hoskins, Adrian Lester, Alexander Siddig(n)

programme.title: Suicide Kings
programme.desc: In this hip crime drama, a spoiled rich teen's (Henry Thomas) sister is abducted, and he and his punk friends decide to kidnap an ex-mob boss (Christopher Walken) as a negotiating tool. But the wily mobster turns the tables on his bungling captors. Denis Leary, Sean Patrick Flanery, Jay Mohr, Jeremy Sisto, Laura San Giacomo(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike XXL
programme.desc: Retired male stripper Magic Mike decides to help his friends put on one last show, as the crew embark on a road trip to Myrtle Beach to perform at an exotic-dance convention. Along the way, they brighten the lives of several women in this sexy sequel(n)

programme.title: Trainwreck
programme.desc: A commitment-phobic binge drinker living in New York City must reevaluate her feelings about intimate relationships when a sports doctor pursues a romance with her(n)

programme.title: The Pyramid
programme.desc: A group of archaeologists discover a lost pyramid in Egypt, and soon end up trapped inside it. Even worse, they realize that a horrific creature is hunting them through the labyrinth. Ashley Hinshaw and Denis O'Hare star as a father/daughter pair of explorers in this claustrophobic fright flick, while James Buckley, Christa Nicola, and Amir K. play the rest of their team. Directed by Gregory Levasseur(n)

programme.title: San Andreas
programme.desc: In this high-octane thriller, the infamous San Andreas Fault gives way, producing a devastating earthquake across California. programme.desc: Strictly Come Dancing's departing head judge Len Goodman recalls the best moments of his dozen years spent arbitrating beneath the glitterball in a documentary celebrating the popular Saturday night programme, as seen through the eyes of one of the genre's greats. Lavishly illustrated with material from the archive, it features contributors including Craig Revel Horwood, Bruno Tonioli, Darcey Bussell, Tess Daly, Jay McGuiness, Claudia Winkleman and Ed Balls reminiscing about Goodman's contribution to the nation's most-loved dancing show.(n)

programme.title: EastEnders
programme.desc: Ben and Louise are confused by Phil's kind behaviour, although another resident sees right through his act and tells him he needs to keep on fighting. It's the second night of the Christmas show, but after the events surrounding the first performance, will the curtain stay firmly shut this evening? Mick and Lee have a heart-to-heart, and it's the end of an era for Dot as she prepares for her retirement party at the launderette.(n)

programme.title: Citizen Khan
programme.desc: Mr Khan revisits his early years, reflecting on the fact that his life hasn't turned out the way he planned it. However, an encounter with a mysterious heavenly passer-by (guest star Lynda Baron) shows him how things might have been different and convinces him that, despite all its frustrations, his is a life worrth living after all. Adil Ray, Shobu Kapoor, Krupa Pattani and Bhavna Limbachia star in a festive episode of the comedy, tipping its hat to Frank Capra's Christmas classic It's a Wonderful Life. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Have I Got News for You
programme.sub-title: Have I Got 2016 News for You.
programme.desc: A compilation of the popular news quiz looking back at the big events of the year. Team captains Ian Hislop and Paul Merton are joined by a variety of guest hosts and panellists. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Walliams & Friend
programme.desc: Miranda Richardson becomes David Walliams' latest `friend', joining forces to play a pair of obnoxious estate agents and a couple on the world's most awkward date. Other sketches see a new company claiming compensation for people who have had their feelings hurt in the workplace, the only person in the world who loves Ant but hates Dec, an obstinate shopper who refuses to pay five pence for a carrier bag, and middle class Jeremy Kyle tackling a man who left the lid off the biscuits. With Morgana Robinson, Mike Wozniak, Jason Lewis, Jocelyn Lee Esien, Kevin Cecil and Joy Richardson.(n)

programme.title: The Graham Norton Show
programme.desc: The host welcomes Will Smith, Helen Mirren and Naomie Harris, who have joined forces in ensemble drama Collateral Beauty. Plus, Doctor Watson himself Martin Freeman talks about the upcoming series of Sherlock, and singer-songwriter Katie Melua performs The Little Swallow. The host also subjects more audience members to the dreaded red chair - so their festive-themed stories had better be good.(n)

programme.title: Mrs Brown's Boys
programme.desc: Having cast herself in the role of the Virgin Mary and with rehearsals in full swing, Agnes vows to make her retelling of the Nativity at the community centre unforgettable. However, Father Damien has yet to approve the script and seems set on offering the role of narrator to Hillary Nicholson - and the doting matriarch has her patience severely tested when her friends and family keep badgering her for the best parts. Festive edition of the comedy first aired in 2012, written by and starring Brendan O'Carroll.(n)

programme.title: The NFL Show
programme.desc: Mark Chapman looks at the major stories shaping the NFL world, joined by former Super Bowl winners Osi Umenyiora and Jason Bell.(n)

programme.title: Signs
programme.desc: A former clergyman who has lost his faith since his wife's death discovers a number of crop circles on his land. Initially believing them to be a prank, he gradually begins to suspect an alien invasion is at hand. As a series of strange and terrifying events takes place, he and his family are forced into hiding in their farmhouse, and must work together to survive. M Night Shyamalan's sci-fi thriller, starring Mel Gibson and Joaquin Phoenix.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: A round-up of national and international news, plus sports reports, weather forecasts and arts and entertainment features. Including NewsWatch at 7.45.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen
programme.desc: John Torode presents the cookery show, joined by chefs Theo Randall and Olia Hercules and actress Charlotte Ritchie, who faces her food heaven or hell.(n)

programme.title: A Christmas Carol
programme.desc: A foul-tempered Victorian miser who hates the festive season is visited on Christmas Eve by a series of ghosts. The spirits intend to make him mend his wicked ways by showing him visions of the past, the present and what the future will hold for him if he does not change for the better. Animated fantasy based on Charles Dickens' novel, featuring motion-captured performances by Jim Carrey and Gary Oldman.(n)

programme.title: Earth's Seasonal Secrets
programme.desc: Documentary exploring how animals all over the world rise to the challenge of surviving the winter. While some creatures face an up-hill struggle to survive, a colder climate plays to the advantage of others, who quickly set about making use of inventive means to seize the huge opportunities the season brings. Caribou become `ice road' travellers as the ground under-foot becomes slippery, and stoats build their own fur beds, snow monkeys set about finding warm baths, and even Emperor penguins - who are build to face extreme low temperatures - find their own way to endure the world's most savage winter conditions. Narrated by Andrew Scott.(n)

programme.title: The Chronicles of Narnia: Prince Caspian
programme.desc: The four Pevensie children are summoned back to the magical land of Narnia to find centuries have passed in their absence. War is now brewing, and the young heroes must help Prince Caspian, the rightful king of Narnia, to overthrow his cruel uncle and reclaim the throne. Fantasy adventure sequel, starring Ben Barnes, William Moseley, Georgie Henley, Skandar Keynes, Anna Popplewell and Peter Dinklage.(n)

programme.title: Shrek the Halls
programme.desc: Festive animated short featuring the full whimsical cast of the hit film series. Shrek settles down for a quiet Christmas with Fiona and the babies, but Donkey and the ogre's other friends have their own ideas - and the party soon descends into chaos. Featuring the voices of Mike Myers, Eddie Murphy, Cameron Diaz and Antonio Banderas.(n)

programme.title: Penguins of Madagascar
programme.desc: Premiere. Heroic flightless birds Skipper, Kowalski, Private and Rico uncover a plot to take over the world. Needing help to foil the evil scheme, they seek out a secret society of animal agents, led by a heroic wolf. Animated comedy spin-off, with the voices of Benedict Cumberbatch, John Malkovich and Tom McGrath.(n)

programme.title: Pointless Celebrities
programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman present a Christmas special of the general knowledge quiz. Taking part are Lesley Joseph, Duncan James, Faye Tozer, Bobby Davro, Joe Pasquale, Wendi Peters, Natasha Hamilton and Keith Chegwin.(n)

programme.title: Michael McIntyre's Big Show
programme.desc: The lively comedian puts a Christmas spin on his weekend variety entertainment show. Broadcast live from London's Theatre Royal on Drury Lane, Michael invites festive favourites Alfie Boe and Michael Ball to perform on-stage. Catherine Tate's foul-mouthed Nan and Harry Enfield's Kevin the Teenager both put in appearances, and Michael seizes Aled Jones' mobile for Send to All. Plus, the comedian stages his most ambitious stunt yet as he surprises an entire choir in Unexpected Star.(n)

programme.title: EastEnders
programme.desc: As Phil contemplates his actions, he is given some tough love by both Shirley and Denise - but he remains adamant he is doing what is best for his family. The final night of the Christmas show is interrupted by devastating family news for Linda. Dot closes up for the final time, and Donna is touched when Carmel invites her to Christmas dinner.(n)

programme.title: David Walliams Celebrates Dame Shirley Bassey
programme.desc: A treat for fans of the veteran singer as comedy actor David Walliams hosts this special night of entertainment paying tribute ahead of her 80th birthday in January. Shirley performs some of her best-loved songs, backed by a live studio orchestra, and also talks to David about her 60-year career, sharing little-known stories and revealing how the girl from Tiger Bay grew up to became one of the most celebrated and distinctive voices in music.(n)

programme.title: Peter Kay's Comedy Shuffle
programme.desc: A festive collection of clips from the comedian's TV career. The programme features highlights from Car Share and Phoenix Nights, as well as a seasonal singalong with Paul McCartney and Geraldine McQueen, which originally took place on Britain's Got the Pop Factor - and Possibly a New Celebrity Jesus Christ Soapstar Superstar Strictly on Ice.(n)

programme.title: The Vicar of Dibley
programme.desc: Alice suggests an unconventional nativity play starring herself and Hugo as Mary and Joseph, and adds an extra touch of authenticity by going into labour mid-performance. The coincidence is so striking that she asks Geraldine whether she has given birth to the Son of God - even though her baby is a girl. Festive episode from 1999, starring Dawn French and Emma Chambers.(n)

programme.title: Midnight Mass: from St Chad's Birmingham
programme.desc: The Most Rev Bernard Longley, Archbishop of Birmingham, leads a traditional Christmas Eve Midnight Mass, broadcast live from St Chad's Cathedral in Birmingham. Features popular carols including Away in a Manger, and In the Bleak Midwinter, as performed by the celebrated St Chad's Cathedral Choir.(n)

programme.title: Christmas City
programme.desc: Rav Wilding and Hayley Hassall investigate what it take to deliver a special Christmas for the shoppers, workers, residents and tourists in Greater Manchester.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Antiques experts Anita Manning and Philip Serrell help two teams search for potentially valuable items at Wetherby Racecourse in West Yorkshire. Presented by Tim Wonnacott.(n)

programme.title: Fern Britton Meets
programme.desc: The former Conservative cabinet member discusses his political career, and the religious beliefs that have underpinned his actions.(n)

programme.title: The Prince and Me
programme.desc: A hard-working teenager is determined to do whatever it takes to become a doctor - but her plans come under threat when she falls in love with a foreign exchange student, who is hiding an interesting secret - he is none other than the prince of Denmark. Romantic comedy, starring Julia Stiles, Luke Mably, Ben Miller, Miranda Richardson and James Fox.(n)

programme.title: Robot Wars
programme.desc: Dara O Briain and Angela Scanlon present more battles between homemade fighting robots, including a towering, sword-wielding warrior built by a Mensa member and his three sons, that is one of the tallest machines to ever enter the arena and runs on wheels that are the height of a washing machine. Other contestants include a mechanical lobster and a 19-year-old self-taught engineer's creation, which has teeth that spin at 9000RPM. The conflict takes a dramatic turn when one of the robots bursts into flames.(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Sarah Moore puts in some hard graft at the nation's tips to uncover four items that can be transformed. Master carpenter Norman Wilkinson, upholsterer Anthony Devine and design guru Jay Blades are on hand to help reinvent the pieces of furniture into desirable pieces. Narrated by Arthur Smith.(n)

programme.title: Sister Act 2: Back in the Habit
programme.desc: A cabaret singer who once hid out in a convent is reunited with the nuns she befriended, who now need her help. She poses as a member of the order once more and joins the staff of a Catholic school threatened with closure, where she aims to make a success of the resident choir. Comedy sequel, starring Whoopi Goldberg, Kathy Najimy, Lauryn Hill, Maggie Smith and James Coburn.(n)

programme.title: Rick Stein's Cornish Christmas
programme.desc: Conclusion. The chef continues his celebrations in his adopted county of Cornwall, using local ingredients to prepare a Christmas banquet for his friends. These include comedian Jethro, an old acquaintance who used to be an adversary on the rugby pitch when they were younger.(n)

programme.title: This Farming Life
programme.desc: Lambing season is just a month away for most of the farmers and to the east of Inverness Martin tends to 500 pregnant ewes and gets the birthing sheds ready with help from his dad Stevie. Further west in Argyll, George takes a group of Belgian hunters out on a deer-stalking trip, and later he and wife Sybil co-host a judging competition where knowledge of blackface sheep is put to the test. In the far north, John heads to the vet with a pedigree ewe that's pregnant with triplets.(n)

programme.title: World's Sneakiest Animals
programme.desc: Chris Packham features animals that utilise devious tactics to win a mate and raise a family, such as bower birds and fiddler crabs, who use optical illusions to impress a female, and male topi antelope, who fake danger to give them an edge. He also looks at family life, including the chicks that blackmail their parents, and the honeyguide bird that dupes another species into raising its young. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Full Steam Ahead
programme.desc: The team discover how the combination of increased leisure time and affordable rail transport brought a new kind of freedom for working-class Victorians. Ruth Goodman travels along the south Devon coast from Paignton to Kingswear, where she helps prepare a paddle steamer for a journey up the River Dart, while at Swanage, Peter Ginn finds out what it was like to work on the excursion trains and the impact mass tourism had on the area. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Porridge
programme.desc: Fletch plans to bring a bit of Christmas spirit to Slade Prison in the form of his own home-made booze. But when Mackay and Barraclough uncover the stash in his cell, the crafty con seems in danger of spending the yuletide period in solitary confinement. Festive edition of the classic comedy from 1976, starring Ronnie Barker and Fulton Mackay.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: Gregg Wallace, Cherry Healey and Ruth Goodman present a special festive edition in which they visit the places where traditional Christmas items roll off the production line. Gregg goes to Britain's biggest cake factory, where 180 million mince pies are produced each year, and pitches in on the Yule log conveyor belt, while Cherry discovers where tinsel and wrapping paper are made.(n)

programme.title: Christmas University Challenge
programme.desc: Representing Edinburgh University, actress Rachael Stirling and geneticist Steve Jones fight it out for a place in the semi-finals against St Catharine's College, Cambridge, which features Radio 4 Today's chief correspondent Matthew Price and novelist Joanne Harris among its numbers. As usual, Jeremy Paxman asks the questions.(n)

programme.title: Wild Tales from the Village
programme.desc: Documentary following the animals that live near a remote rural French village, including red squirrels, wild boar, dormice and stone martens. As the wildlife struggles to survive the winter, they take full advantage of living so close to unsuspecting humans in their search for food, while trying not to be detected. Narrated by Tcheky Karyo.(n)

programme.title: Saving Mr Banks
programme.desc: Premiere. Walt Disney becomes determined to adapt Mary Poppins into a film, but faces an obstacle in the shape of author PL Travers, who resists the idea of a sentimental Hollywood version of her book. As the movie mogul's charm offensive comes unstuck, he begins to realise why the story is so important to its creator. Fact-based drama, with Emma Thompson, Tom Hanks, Paul Giamatti and Colin Farrell.(n)

programme.title: Mock the Week
programme.desc: Host Dara O Briain is back with the comedy panel show's traditional helping of seasonal silliness. As well as the usual mix of out-takes, highlights and unseen material, there's a Christmas quiz, a festive Scenes We'd Like to See, a seasonal newsreel from Hugh Dennis and a guest appearance from a somewhat sinister teddy bear. With contributions from Josh Widdicombe, Holly Walsh, Rob Beckett, Katherine Ryan, Ed Byrne, Romesh Ranganathan and Sara Pascoe, and even something a little bit different in the opening titles too.(n)

programme.title: Close to the Enemy
programme.desc: As preparations for Dieter's wedding get under way, Kathy finally confronts Bergit about her activities, forcing the prisoner to realise her options are limited. Harold makes a decisive move as he struggles with his feelings of inadequacy, and Victor continues to be haunted by the effects of war. Callum is concerned he is caught up in a marital game, and forces Rachel to admit her true feelings for him. Jim Sturgess stars in Stephen Poliakoff's drama. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: And Now for Something Completely Different
programme.desc: The Monty Python members appear in their first movie, comprising re-enacted sketches from the first two series of the surreal comedy show. Highlights include the dead parrot sketch, the Lumberjack Song and the Upper-class Twit of the Year Race. Starring the usual team of John Cleese, Michael Palin, Graham Chapman, Eric Idle, Terry Jones and Terry Gilliam, with regular female sidekick Carol Cleveland.(n)

programme.title: Darcey Bussell: Looking for Margot
programme.desc: Margot Fonteyn inspired generations of ballerinas, while her late-flowering partnership with Rudolf Nureyev created the most dazzling ballet partnership in history. However, her life was marked by tragedy and disappointment. Darcey finds that Margot couldn't find love and never had children, got drawn into a failed foreign revolution, danced on for too long, and died in poverty. The former time ballerina goes behind the scenes at the Royal Opera House and the Royal Ballet, and travels from London to New York and Panama, discovering that Margot did eventually find a kind of happiness - though one that came at a high price.(n)

programme.title: Back in Time for Brixton
programme.desc: Part two of two. The Irwins experience life in the 1970s, '80s and '90s, discovering how a new generation of black Britons made their way through three decades of British history, guided by presenter Giles Coren and social historian Emma Dabiri. They meet former West Indies cricket captain Clive Lloyd and learn about the 1976 tour of England in which he led his side to victory, before reflecting on the Brixton Riots of the 1980s, and hosting a typical 1989-style party with DJ and producer Jazzie B of Soul II Soul.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: Mars Needs Moms
programme.desc: A nine-year-old boy sees a spacecraft land and kidnap his mother. He stows away on board as the ship travels back to the aliens' Mars homeland. As he tries to rescue her, he learns the Martians have taken her because they need Earth mothers to raise their own children. Animated sci-fi adventure, with the voices of Seth Robert Dusky, Dan Fogler and Joan Cusack.(n)

programme.title: The NFL Show
programme.desc: Mark Chapman looks at the major stories shaping the NFL world, joined by former Super Bowl winners Osi Umenyiora and Jason Bell.(n)

programme.title: Hans Christian Andersen
programme.desc: A children's storyteller is chased out of his small village to the Danish capital Copenhagen. At first daunted by the hustle and bustle, he soon overcomes his fear and falls in love with a ballerina. Musical, starring Danny Kaye, Zizi Jeanmaire and Farley Granger and featuring the songs Thumbelina, The Ugly Duckling, Wonderful Copenhagen and The Emperor's New Clothes.(n)

programme.title: Robot Wars
programme.desc: Dara O Briain and Angela Scanlon present the final, featuring the five heat winners and one of the runners-up. Judges Sethu Vijayakumar, Noel Sharkey and Dr Lucy Rodgers decide the winner, while Jonathan Pearce provides commentary on the mayhem.(n)

programme.title: Wallace & Gromit: A Close Shave
programme.desc: Nick Park's Oscar-winning animated characters embark on their third adventure. Wallace falls in love with the proprietor of the local wool shop - only for Gromit to be framed for sheep rustling. With the voices of Peter Sallis and Anne Reid.(n)

programme.title: Nigella's Christmas Kitchen
programme.sub-title: Life in the Old Bird Yet?.
programme.desc: Nigella Lawson tries to ensure kitchen-duty during the festive season remains fun by demonstrating how to cook the perfect spiced roast turkey. She also reveals how to put together an accompaniment of pancetta and chestnut sprouts, maple syrup parsnips, and gingerbread stuffing, followed by Fanny Cradock's recipe for vodka-flamed Christmas pudding.(n)

programme.title: The Cook Who Changed Our Lives
programme.desc: Nigella Lawson narrates this profile of Milanese cook and food writer Anna Del Conte, now aged 91, whose recipe books changed Britain's attitudes to Italian food at a time when olive oil could only be bought at the chemist. With contributions from Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall, Antonio Carluccio, Prue Leith, Loyd Grossman and Tom Parker Bowles.(n)

programme.title: Splash
programme.desc: A lonely New Yorker is rescued from drowning by a mermaid, who falls in love with him and assumes human form so she can seek him out in Manhattan. He is soon equally smitten, and she resolves to keep her true nature a secret from him. However, an obsessive scientist suspects the truth and plans to prove it. Romantic fantasy comedy, starring Tom Hanks, Daryl Hannah and John Candy.(n)

programme.title: Snow Chick: A Penguin's Tale
programme.desc: Documentary following the first few months in the life of an emperor penguin born in an Antarctic midwinter. Kate Winslet narrates as cameras follow the young bird, watching him learn to survive the dangers of predators and the treacherous landscape of his home, before he is thrown into the ocean for the very first time.(n)

programme.title: Gorilla Family and Me
programme.desc: Part one of two. Wildlife cameraman Gordon Buchanan travels to the Democratic Republic of the Congo, where he realises a lifelong dream by spending time with Grauer's gorillas, the largest primates on earth. He meets the fearsome alpha male Chimanuka and two babies, one a lonely orphan and as Gordon gains the trust of these mysterious, seldom seen animals, he discovers their incredible compassion and gets caught up in a battle between giant rival silverbacks for control of the family.(n)

programme.title: Gorilla Family and Me
programme.desc: Part two of two. Gordon Buchanan returns to the Democratic Republic of Congo in the hope of finding the gorilla family again, and discovering the outcome of silverback Chimanuka's confrontation with a rival. He soon finds the apes, but discovers their lives are now under threat from poachers, and works with the local rangers to prevent them coming to harm.(n)

programme.title: Carols from King's
programme.desc: The solo chorister singing the opening verse of Once in Royal David's City marks the start of this annual service from the Chapel of King's College, Cambridge. The world-famous Choir of King's College performs a selection of carols, including Ding! Dong! Merrily on High (Wilberg), The Holly and the Ivy, The Three Kings (Cornelius), and O Come All Ye Faithful, as directed by Stephen Cleobury. The songs are interspersed by readings of the Christmas story from the King James Bible, along with poems by Charles Causley, UA Fanthorpe, and former Archbishop of Canterbury Rowan Williams.(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: The platoon challenges a rival regiment to a gruelling duel, involving map-reading, initiative tests, river-crossing and field-fighting, to prove they are fitter and better trained than any other troop. Vintage comedy with the bumbling Home Guard of Walmington-on-Sea, starring Arthur Lowe, John Le Mesurier and Ian Lavender.(n)

programme.title: Alan Bennett's Diaries
programme.desc: Candid profile of the writer, following him both in his home village in Yorkshire and during a trip to New York. In a series of intimate encounters, he discusses his humble beginnings, his 23-year relationship with his partner, and his feelings on modern politics.(n)

programme.title: The Lady in the Van
programme.desc: The true story of writer Alan Bennett's friendship with an eccentric homeless woman, whom he befriended in the 1970s before allowing her to park her dilapidated Bedford van outside his Camden home, where she ended up staying for 15 years. Comedy-drama, starring Maggie Smith, Alex Jennings, Roger Allam and Jim Broadbent.(n)

programme.title: The National Lottery Live
programme.desc: The all-important winning numbers are revealed.(n)

programme.title: TOTP2
programme.desc: Mark Radcliffe returns with another trawl through the archives of Top of the Pops, introducing a feast of festive delights from the BBC vaults including performances by Blur, Pretenders, the Bluebells, Katie Melua, Paul McCartney and Kurtis Blow. There's a classic rendition of Baby It's Cold Outside by Cerys Matthews and Tom Jones, as well as perennial yuletide favourites from the likes of Slade, Wham!, Wizzard, East 17, Mud, the Jackson 5 and Johnny Mathis, and rarely seen footage of Kate Bush extolling the delights of December and the festive season.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: John Peel introduces performances by Modern Romance, Duran Duran, Blancmange, Renee and Renato, Wham, Eddy Grant, Tears for Fears and Hall & Oates.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: Peter Powell introduces performances by Kevin Roland and Dexys Midnight Runners, Human League, Whitesnake, Bucks Fizz, Modern Romance, Duran Duran and the Jam.(n)

programme.title: Darcey Bussell: My Life on the BBC
programme.desc: For 20 years, Britain's premier dancer with the Royal Ballet was documented at regular intervals throughout her ballet career by BBC cameras, and also appeared on many of the Corporation's biggest entertainment shows. Here, her life story is told through a carefully woven choice of archive, from her debut appearance on Blue Peter as a 16-year-old to jiving on Strictly Come Dancing following her retirement as a ballerina in 2007.(n)

programme.title: The Old Grey Whistle Test
programme.desc: Highlights from the 1970s music series, including performances by Elton John and David Bowie, and featuring an early UK TV appearance from Curtis Mayfield. Plus music by New York Dolls, Steppenwolf's iconic Born to be Wild and 1973 hits from Roxy Music, The Wailers and Vinegar Joe. The programme's finale celebrates the advent of punk and new wave with performances from Patti Smith, Blondie, Iggy Pop and The Jam.(n)

programme.title: Joy of Abba
programme.desc: Documentary exploring how pop group Abba raised the bar for their music genre in the 1970s and early 80s, popularising the sound of Swedish melancholy. The programme explores how the quartet of Agnetha Faltskog, Bjorn Ulvaeus, Benny Andersson and Anni-Frid Lyngstad came to dominate the British music charts with simple, catchy melodies, but also divided opinion due to the populist sheen of their output.(n)

programme.title: Queens of Disco
programme.desc: Graham Norton celebrates the careers of some of the greatest names in disco music, including Gloria Gaynor, Donna Summer, Grace Jones and Chaka Khan. He also explores Madonna's return to her 1980s roots and the success it brought her in the UK pop charts.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: John Peel introduces performances by Modern Romance, Duran Duran, Blancmange, Renee and Renato, Wham, Eddy Grant, Tears for Fears and Hall & Oates.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: Peter Powell introduces performances by Kevin Roland and Dexys Midnight Runners, Human League, Whitesnake, Bucks Fizz, Modern Romance, Duran Duran and the Jam.(n)

programme.title: Darcey Bussell: My Life on the BBC
programme.desc: For 20 years, Britain's premier dancer with the Royal Ballet was documented at regular intervals throughout her ballet career by BBC cameras, and also appeared on many of the Corporation's biggest entertainment shows. Here, her life story is told through a carefully woven choice of archive, from her debut appearance on Blue Peter as a 16-year-old to jiving on Strictly Come Dancing following her retirement as a ballerina in 2007.(n)

programme.title: Joy of Abba
programme.desc: Documentary exploring how pop group Abba raised the bar for their music genre in the 1970s and early 80s, popularising the sound of Swedish melancholy. The programme explores how the quartet of Agnetha Faltskog, Bjorn Ulvaeus, Benny Andersson and Anni-Frid Lyngstad came to dominate the British music charts with simple, catchy melodies, but also divided opinion due to the populist sheen of their output.(n)

programme.title: All Aboard! The Sleigh Ride
programme.desc: A two-hour sleigh ride filmed in Karasjok, Norway - 200 miles north of the Arctic Circle - filmed from point of view of the reindeer herder travelling across the frozen wilderness. Following the path of an ancient postal route, the ride captures the traditional world of the Sami people who are indigenous to northern Scandinavia and for whom reindeer herding remains a way of life.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops
programme.sub-title: Top of the Pops Christmas Hits.
programme.desc: A collection of chart-toppers from festive episodes of the music show, including the first-ever repeat showing of a recently rediscovered 1967 performance by the Rolling Stones. The programme also features perennial Christmas classics from the likes of Slade, Mud and Frankie Goes to Hollywood, as well as Ian Dury & the Blockheads, Madness, East 17, Coldplay, the Human League and the Pet Shop Boys.(n)

programme.title: Roy Orbison: One of the Lonely Ones
programme.desc: Biography of the singer and musician, casting new light on the triumphs and tragedies that beset his career, featuring performances and home movies, and providing an insight into Orbison's remote Texas childhood and his battles to get his voice heard. This film reveals how his rollercoaster life was often reflected in the dark lyrics of his songs, from success to rejection, and rediscovery in the 1980s with the Travelling Wilburys supergroup. Featuring interviews with Jeff Lynne, T Bone Burnett, Bobby Goldsboro and Marianne Faithfull.(n)

programme.title: Steptoe and Son
programme.desc: Christmas special from 1974. Ever the optimist, Harold again plans to spend Christmas abroad, but doesn't count on Albert's intransigence. In predictable fashion, the old man takes umbrage at the thought of being left behind in Shepherd's Bush, and insists on inviting himself along. Harry H Corbett and Wilfrid Brambell star in the last ever episode of the sitcom.(n)

programme.title: Irish Rally Review
programme.desc: Highlights of the Killarney Historic Rally, part of the Irish Rally series.(n)

programme.title: Rugby Tonight
programme.desc: In this Christmas special, Sarra Elgan is joined by Ben Kay, Ugo Monye, David Flatman and Quins' Luke Wallace to discuss all things rugby and preview the upcoming festive fixtures.(n)

programme.title: Global Goals
programme.desc: This week's best goals, including Mario Balotelli's brace, a sensational effort from Gonzalo Higuain and a stunning haul from Napoli's Dries Mertens against Joe Hart's Torino side.(n)

programme.title: Live Hyundai A-League

programme.title: Christmas with the Double Acts
programme.desc: An hour of festive fun featuring stand-out comedy moments from some of the greatest double acts to have graced the small screen, with famous fans and colleagues revealing just what makes them so funny. Those featured include Morecambe and Wise, French and Saunders, the Two Ronnies, Ant and Dec, Cannon and Ball, and Little and Large - as well as fictional duos George and Mildred, Cissie and Ada, Smashie and Nicey, and Wallace and Gromit.(n)

programme.title: The Morecambe and Wise Story: Look Back in Laughter
programme.desc: Documentary making use of old performances, chat-show appearances and archive interviews to shed light on the success of Eric Morecambe and Ernie Wise. The film explores the pair's working-class roots in the north of England, and their early encounters. Eric's mother Sadie claimed to be the first person to spot their potential as a comedy double-act when, as children, they spent an entire train journey to Coventry annoying her with their antics. The Second World War would see the duo split up, but they were reunited by chance, and by 1968 they had become established household names, and were on track to become the most-watched comedy act in the history of British TV.(n)

programme.title: Morecambe & Wise Live! 1973
programme.desc: The duo's performance at the Ashcroft Theatre in Croydon's Fairfield Halls in October 1973, which was the only one of their stage shows captured on film. Backed by the Johnny Wiltshire Sound, Eric and Ernie make their entrance to the familiar strains of Bring Me Sunshine, before entertaining the audience with a mix of sketches, one-liners and musical numbers honed during many years on the comedy circuit.(n)

programme.title: The Peter Kay Story
programme.desc: Documentary tracing the career of one of Britain's best-loved and most successful comedians, charting his journey from humble beginnings to superstardom. Featuring contributions from people who know him or have worked with him, as well as his fans and biographers.(n)

programme.desc: A selection of comedians and celebrities, including Anthea Turner, Vanessa Feltz, Carl Fogarty, Kerry Godliman, Louisa Lytton, Vikki Stone, James Acaster and the appropriately named Jarred Christmas, discuss everything they love and loathe about the festive season. Plus, Johnny Vegas helps steer viewers through the minefield of Christmas rituals and traditions.(n)

The music features classics such as White Christmas, Have Yourself a Merry Little Christmas, Jingle Bells, This Christmas and Here Comes Santa Claus. programme.desc: Estate agent Ann Maurice offers her expertise to a couple whose home in Rothwell near Leeds is still for sale after 10 months, despite having attracted more than 30 viewings. programme.desc: Absent-minded witch Winnie and her loyal black cat Wilbur embark on a series of hair-raising wintery escapades, caused by Winnie's unpredictable magic. Animated comedy, with the voices of Kary Brand and Bill Bailey.(n)

programme.title: Ben and Holly's Little Kingdom

programme.title: Doctor Zhivago
programme.desc: A married Russian physician falls in love with another woman, but as their passionate affair plays out against the raging backdrop of the First World War and the Bolshevik revolution, he is torn between his desires and his loyalty to his wife. David Lean's epic drama based on Boris Pasternak's novel, starring Omar Sharif, Julie Christie, Geraldine Chaplin, Rod Steiger, Alec Guinness, Ralph Richardson, Tom Courtenay and Klaus Kinski. Edited for language.(n)

programme.title: The Vikings
programme.desc: A Norse warrior becomes embroiled in a feud with a former slave over the succession to the Northumbrian throne, unaware his arch-enemy is really his half-brother. Matters come to a head when they both set their sights on a Welsh princess, leading to a confrontation - but the situation is further complicated by the interference of England's sadistic king. Adventure, with Kirk Douglas, Tony Curtis, Janet Leigh, Ernest Borgnine and James Donald.(n)

programme.title: Jason and the Argonauts
programme.desc: The son of an overthrown king must embark on an epic sea voyage in search of the fabled Golden Fleece so he can return and reclaim his kingdom. Before he can seize the treasure, he has to overcome a series of horrific creatures, including a seven-headed monster and a horde of sword-wielding skeletons. Mythological fantasy adventure, starring Todd Armstrong, Honor Blackman, Nancy Kovack, Niall MacGinnis and Patrick Troughton, with special effects by Ray Harryhausen. Includes 5 News at 4.05pm.(n)

programme.title: Scrooge - A Christmas Carol
programme.desc: A hard-hearted skinflint refuses to join in with the spirit of the festive season - until a succession of spectral visitors teaches him the error of his ways by showing him visions of the past, present and future. Adaptation of Charles Dickens' A Christmas Carol, starring Alastair Sim, Mervyn Johns, Kathleen Harrison, Jack Warner, Michael Hordern, Hermione Baddeley, Hattie Jacques and George Cole. Includes 5 News at 6.10pm.(n)

programme.title: Andre Rieu: Christmas in London
programme.desc: A festive concert given by the Dutch violinist and the Johann Strauss Orchestra in 2015, featuring Christmas carols, popular classical pieces and songs including Leonard Cohen's Hallelujah and the Concierto de Aranjuez.(n)

programme.title: The Yorkshire Vet
programme.desc: The veterinary documentary series concludes with a festive trip to Skeldale. Elderly farmer Jean, one of the show's most colourful characters, makes a Christmas cake with ingredients that have been `maturing' for seven years, and vet Peter Wright fears the worst when he is called to tend to a cow that has collapsed. Back at the surgery, Julian Norton has to make a difficult decision regarding Barney, a spaniel with a huge, fast-growing tumour on his leg. The residents of Thirsk plan to mark James Herriot's centenary by inviting his successors to turn on the town's Christmas lights, but Julian and Peter face a more daunting challenge when they are asked to help find a donkey for the town square nativity scene. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Eamonn & Ruth: How the Other Half Lives
programme.sub-title: Eamonn & Ruth: A Million Pound Christmas.
programme.desc: Eamonn Holmes and Ruth Langsford discover the most expensive ways in which people can enjoy the season of goodwill, beginning by sampling a £10,000 advent calendar, populated with rare miniature whiskies. Another festive trinket gets a million-pound makeover in the form of the world's first diamond crackers, with each containing a real gem. Eamonn meets the heir to the Cointreau throne to share a classy, festive cocktail, before suiting up to discover what it takes to be a bona fide Santa. As the pair discover, even wrapping paper can go over the top, with sheets smothered in Swarovski crystals costing £20,000 each.(n)

programme.title: Greatest Ever Christmas Movies
programme.desc: Countdown of the best festive films, from White Christmas and It's a Wonderful Life to Bad Santa and Elf. Gremlins star Zach Galligan and Miracle on 34th Street's Mara Wilson talk about their experiences making their movies, while Aled Jones reveals that he hadn't even seen classic animation The Snowman until nearly 20 years after having a hit in 1985 with a version of its famous song Walking in the Air. Featuring contributions by Ollie Locke, Stacey Solomon, Joe Swash and Eamonn Holmes.(n)

programme.title: The Wrestler

programme.title: Formula 51
programme.desc: First-time screenwriter Stelios Pavlou enjoyed a major success with this script that he wrote while working in an English liquor store by sending it to actor Samuel L. Jackson, who signed on for one of the lead roles. Jackson is Elmo McElroy, a kilt-wearing, golf club-wielding Los Angeles native who has invented an illegal drug formula that he hopes will provide him with a last major score of 20 million dollars before he retires from a life of crime. He travels to Liverpool, England, where he hopes to find a buyer for his creation among the denizens of the city's rave scene, but his plans go awry when those who are in on the deal start turning up dead. Elmo's only protector is a chain-smoking, Yank-hating local hood named Felix De Souza (Robert Carlyle), who reluctantly partners with the violence-prone American to finish the deal and cash in, sparking a gang war between Elmo's vengeful one-time employer, The Lizard (Meat Loaf); Felix's boss, Durant (Ricky Tomlinson); crooked cop Virgil Kane (Sean Pertwee); a beautiful assassin, who also happens to be Felix's ex-girlfriend (Emily Mortimer); and an offbeat, yoga-practicing nightclub owner and mobster named Iki (Rhys Ifans). For its U.S. release, the title of The 51st State was changed to Formula 51(n)

In this inspiring biopic, Jackie Robinson breaks Major League Baseball's color barrier when he is signed to the Brooklyn Dodgers by the team's forward-thinking general manager, Branch Rickey. The gifted athlete deals with tremendous pressure and threats from racist fans and players, but perseveres to become a legendary baseball player and a heroic figure in American history(n)

programme.title: Down to Earth
programme.desc: Chris Rock rolls into reincarnation madness in this comedy based on 1978's "Heaven Can Wait." When a heavenly mix-up causes struggling black stand-up comic Lance Barton (Rock) to die before his time, he is sent back down to the mortal world in the form of a rich---and white---old-timer named Charles Wellington. Regina King, Chazz Palminteri, Eugene Levy, Frankie Faison(n)

programme.title: Speed Racer
programme.desc: The Matrix masterminds Andy and Larry Wachowski usher anime icon Tatsuo Yoshida's classic 1960s-era hit into the new millennium with this family-friendly story of a young racecar driver who takes on the mysterious Racer X in a custom-made, gadget-loaded speed machine named the Mach 5 . Speed Racer (Emile Hirsch) is the kind of driver that every wheelman wishes he could be: a born winner whose unbeatable combination of aggression, instinct, and fearlessness always finds him crossing the checkered flag with a comfortable lead. In Speed Racer's mind, the only driver who could present him with any real challenge is his late brother -- the legendary Rex Racer. Rex died in a heated cross-country rally known as The Crucible many years ago, and now his younger sibling is driven to fulfill the legacy that Rex left behind. To this day, Speed Racer is fiercely loyal to family. It was Speed Racer's father, Pops Racer (John Goodman), who designed the unbeatable Mach 5 , and even a lucrative offer from racing giants Royalton Industries isn't enough to get the young ace to break his family ties. Upon turning down Royalton's (Roger Allam) astronomical offer, Speed Racer makes the shocking discovery that the outcomes of the biggest races are being predetermined by a handful of powerful moguls who pad their profits by manipulating the drivers. Realizing that his career would be ruined if word of the fix gets out, Royalton vows that the Mach 5 will never make it to another finish line. Now, the only way for Speed Racer to save the family business and beat Royalton at his own game will be to win the very same race that claimed his brother's life so many years ago. In order to accomplish that formidable feat, however, Speed Racer will not only have to rely on his family and the aid of his longtime girlfriend, Trixie (Christina Ricci), but form a tenuous alliance with his longtime rival -- the mysterious Racer X (Matthew Fox) -- as well(n)

programme.desc: Homer causes havoc when he pollutes Lake Springfield to dangerous levels. When the toxic town gets sealed under a giant glass dome, it looks like the end for the people of Springfield. Can the Simpson family save the day?(n)

programme.desc: Twenty-two years after Jurassic Park opened on Isla Nubar, a dinosaur-themed resort attracts thousands of visitors each year, just as John Hammond envisioned. Like his father, Clark (Chevy Chase), Rusty wants to forge closer bonds with his own family - wife Debbie (Christina Applegate) and boys James and Kevin (Skyler Gisondo and Steele Stebbins) - so he buys a souped-up Albanian van and convinces them to set off on their own crazy cross-country jaunt to Walley World. Carrey stars as television reporter Bruce Nolan. Despite his status as a well-liked minor celebrity and the unconditional love of his beautiful girlfriend, Grace (Jennifer Aniston), Bruce can't seem to shake his dissatisfaction with the shortfalls of his everyday life. After an exceptionally misfortune-filled day, Bruce turns to the sky and lays into God, accusing Him of doing a poor job of running things on Earth. Bruce is so vehement that God (Morgan Freeman) transports Bruce to his office and makes him a once-in-a-lifetime offer. If Bruce thinks He is so inadequate, God tells him that he'll bestow omnipotence upon Bruce for 24 hours. However, if by the end of that period of time Bruce is unsuccessful in his attempts to make the world a better place, as a consequence, God will inflict a cataclysm upon Earth that will revert things back to the Dark Ages. programme.sub-title: Dead Woman Walking: The Karla Faye Tucker Story
programme.desc: Dead Woman Walking: The Karla Faye Tucker Story. This documentary, part of the American Justice series from A&E, examines the Texas death penalty case of Karla Faye Walker. Narrated by American Justice host and producer Bill Kurtis, this episode goes inside the investigation of the two murders that Walker and her boyfriend Daniel Ryan Garrett committed. The trial of Walker is shown through exclusive footage. After the conviction, American Justice follows her through her daily life, showing her prison surroundings and talking with her about her crimes. Sentenced to death, while Walker was waiting to be executed, she became a born-again Christian. Her lawyers used this transformation as leverage to try to get her death sentence reduced to life in prison. Their attempts were unsuccessful and Walker was killed by lethal injection in February 1998. American Justice also shows interviews with lawyers and law enforcement professionals who knew Walker(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: Naturalist David Attenborough documents the universal tale that unites humanity with every other animal on the planet - the journey through life, and the goal to continue the bloodline through offspring. This edition focuses on the first hurdle any animal will face, surviving infancy. Cameras follow flightless barnacle goose chicks as they strive to find food, leaping 400ft down a cliff from the ledge where they hatched. Meanwhile, in New Zealand, young fur seals have stumbled across a safe haven in which they can learn how to avoid predators, while deep in the Gobi Desert, the long-eared jerboa learns to use its impeccable hearing to catch insect pray. Plus, albatross chicks make their first flight, as threatening tiger sharks wait patiently for them to slip up and land in the sea.(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: David Attenborough details the transition animals go through as they grow into adults. Looking at examples including a tiger cub whose family is under threat, a vulnerable veined octopus and a pair of sibling cheetahs guarding against starvation, the veteran naturalist illustrates how they develop new skills and learn how to survive on their own.(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: The importance of homes to animals, not only as a place to live but as a shelter from the elements and a refuge from enemies. A pack of African hunting dogs have made their home on a vast plain in Zambia, but it's far from safe as they must battle hyenas and protect their young. Hermit crabs on a tropical island settle down in empty snail shells - and when a new property washes ashore, they all form a queue, then move up the housing chain until all the shells are taken. On the edge of the Sahara are chimpanzees, whose survival relies on knowing where to find water in the most extreme droughts. Here the elders lead a troop on a brutal trek to a dried-out riverbed to dig wells.(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: The importance of power in the animal kingdom, revealing how dominant creatures have the best access to food and water, and are also the most attractive to the opposite sex. An orphaned young chimp tries to climb the social ladder, but his troop is ruled by big, aggressive males and his first attempt to join them ends in a beating. A meerkat society will only allow newcomers in if they know how to deal with a venomous snake. And the only way to occupy the top spot in a meadow of kangaroos is to beat the ruling male in a boxing match - but few have challenged the current incumbent, who stands at 8ft. Will any animal dare take him on? David Attenborough narrates.(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: David Attenborough reveals how the competition to breed creates scenes of the most extraordinary beauty, as well as some of the most violent battles seen in nature. A male flame bowerbird shows off its artistic prowess to impress a potential mate - but if that does not prove enough, it will demonstrate its dancing skills instead. Waved albatrosses pair up for life and spend hours in each other's company, although things are not so simple for a male peacock jumping spider - one wrong move in its dazzling courtship routine could prove fatal. However, one of the most magnificent displays of all is created by a tiny male pufferfish, which impresses the ladies by building a spectacular underwater `crop circle' in the sand - arguably the most perfect and complex structure created by any animal.(n)

programme.title: Life Story
programme.desc: David Attenborough's documentary charting the circle of life in the animal kingdom ends with creatures' attempts to rear their offspring, revealing the commitment involved and how for some parents it means risking their own lives. A turtle hauls itself up the beach to lay its eggs in a safe place, only for the tide to trap it behind a wall of coral. A mother bonobo in the Congo teaches its son the skills it will need to survive adulthood, bison protect their calves from the ever-present threat of wolves and a mother zebra has to lead its foal across a dangerous river. Last in the series.(n)
